        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> The big issue i have with mana vs lifeburn is the risk factor invloved in each.  </P><P>A mana burn is an extremely low risk/low agro event that is often followed by the wizzie chewing up a few rods, and medding back to FM to unleash another 20k dmg on a mob.  </P><P>A necro will lifeburn relatively late in a fight, after exhausting the majority of his mana and generate tremendous agro due to the existing dmg inflicted and also due to the low hp level after a burn is executed.</P><P>If things are are generally based on risk vs reward in EQ, then VI should look into either reducing the risk of a lifeburn, or increasing its potential reward (dmg output).  Really i'd recommend two things.  Firstly the possibility to crit and secondly, having the secondary dot do as much dmg as the initial dd.  So if necro x lifeburns for 4k dmg, the lifetap dot should also be for 4k dmg also.</P><P>Wizzies dont die after a burn, they just need to chew up a few rods and med to get back into the fight.  Necro's on the other hand need to take a number of preventative steps to reduce the chance of an instant death on a burn.  Given this risk, i feel that the dmg output/potential of a lifeburn should be increased dramatically.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55675" target="_blank">Tencor Laureate - 60th Warlock</a><br><BR><a href="http://www.veilofsilence.org" target="_blank">Veil of Silence</a><br> <BR>Innoruuk Server</font></td>
